fect translations, the book draws on the broad experiences of its contributors—all of whom are translators themselves—who bring different themes to the table. Each chapter can be used either independently or as part of the whole to engender reflections on the process of translation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aBuddhist literaturezSouth AsiaxHistory and criticism. 0aBuddhist literaturezSouth AsiaxTranslations into English. 0aTranslating and interpretingxReligious aspectsxBuddhism. 0aTranslators. 4aLanguage Arts : Linguistics. 4aLiterature : Translation. 4aReligion and Spirituality : Buddhism. 7aRELIGION / Buddhism / History.2bisacsh1 aCollett, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCollett, Alice, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCox, Collett, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGamage, Aruna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGummer, Natalie, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHarris, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHinüber, Oskar von, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, C. V., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJones, Dhivan Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLangenberg, Amy Paris, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLugli, Ligeia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2021z978311149169140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143848295840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438482958423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/97814384829